---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Did the Parties Switch?
description: Yes. Here's the proof. Primary sources from 1861 to 2024 tracking the voters who opposed civil rights, from the Democratic Party to the Republican Party.
---

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 1: THE OPENING
   ============================================ #}
<section class="hero" id="chapter-intro" data-chapter="Introduction">
  <div class="hero__vignette"></div>
  <div class="hero__content-wrapper">
    <div class="hero__eyebrow">
      <span class="hero__line"></span>
      <span class="hero__date-text">1861 — 2024</span>
      <span class="hero__line"></span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="headline-hero hero__title">
      <span class="hero__title-line">Yes, the Parties</span>
      <span class="hero__title-line hero__title-line--accent">Switched.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="subheadline hero__subtitle">
      The evidence from 1861 to today. Their own words. Their own votes.
    </p>
    <div class="hero__cta">
      <a href="#chapter-spark" class="btn btn--primary btn--large">See the Proof</a>
      <a href="/quiz/" class="btn btn--ghost">Take the Quiz</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="scroll-prompt">
    <span class="scroll-prompt__text">Scroll to explore</span>
    <span class="scroll-prompt__arrow">↓</span>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   MISSION STATEMENT
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-mission" data-chapter="Mission">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--narrow reveal">
      <div class="mission-statement">
        <p class="mission-statement__text">{{ site.mission }}</p>
        <p class="mission-statement__scope"><strong>Scope:</strong> {{ site.scope }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 2: THE SPARK
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--muted" id="chapter-spark" data-chapter="The Spark">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter I</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">The Spark That Lit the War</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        At 4:30 a.m., Confederate batteries opened fire on Fort Sumter.
        The Union garrison had not fired a single shot.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-sumter">
  <div class="fact-stack">
    <article class="fact-item reveal">
      <span class="fact-item__number">01</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">The First Shots</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        Confederate commander P.G.T. Beauregard ordered the bombardment of Fort Sumter at 4:30 a.m.
        on April 12, 1861. Major Robert Anderson's Union garrison endured 34 hours before
        evacuating. The Confederacy fired first; the Union did not fire on Confederates before this
        attack.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="fact-item reveal reveal--delay-1">
      <span class="fact-item__number">02</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">The Secession Wave</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        Between December 1860 and June 1861, eleven states declared secession. Each public
        declaration cited threats to slavery, often by name. No hidden code, just explicit intent.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="fact-item reveal reveal--delay-2">
      <span class="fact-item__number">03</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">The Cornerstone</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        On March 21, 1861, Confederate Vice President Alexander Stephens told Savannah that the
        Confederacy rested on "the great truth that the negro is not equal to the white man."
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 3: THE DOCUMENTS
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--gradient" id="chapter-documents" data-chapter="Their Words">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter II</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">What They Actually Said</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        The secession documents leave no room for debate. They stated their cause explicitly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Mississippi Quote - Full Screen #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="quote-block reveal">
      <blockquote class="quote-block__text">
        Our position is thoroughly identified with the institution of slavery, the greatest material
        interest of the world.
      </blockquote>
      <cite class="quote-block__attribution">- Mississippi Declaration of Secession, January 1861</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Primary Source Cards #}
<section class="chapter chapter--muted" id="chapter-sources" data-chapter="Sources">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Primary Sources</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">Read the Documents</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        Direct quotes from secession documents, speeches, and official records.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--full">
      <div class="source-grid">
        {% for source in primarySources %}
        <article class="source-card reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 3 }}">
          <div class="source-card__header">
            <span class="source-card__date">{{ source.date }}</span>
            <div class="source-card__icon">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"></path>
                <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"></polyline>
                <line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"></line>
                <line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"></line>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="source-card__title">{{ source.title }}</h3>
          {% if source.contentWarning %}
          <div class="content-warning content-warning--compact">
            <span class="content-warning__label">Content Warning:</span>
            <span class="content-warning__text">{{ source.warningText }}</span>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
          <blockquote class="source-card__quote">"{{ source.quote }}"</blockquote>
          <footer class="source-card__footer">
            <cite class="source-card__attribution">{{ source.attribution }}</cite>
            <div class="source-card__links">
              <a href="{{ source.link }}" class="source-card__link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                {{ source.linkText }}
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"></path>
                  <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline>
                  <line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"></line>
                </svg>
              </a>
              {% if source.archiveLink %}
              <a href="{{ source.archiveLink }}" class="source-card__archive" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Archived backup copy">
                Archived
              </a>
              {% endif %}
            </div>
            {% if source.isGovernment %}
            <p class="source-card__warning">Government source - verified intact Dec 2025</p>
            {% endif %}
          </footer>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Document Analysis - Word Count - All Four States #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-numbers" data-chapter="The Numbers">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Numbers Don't Lie</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">Count the Words Across All Four Declarations</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        Four states issued formal declarations explaining their secession. Here's what they talked about.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide">
      <div class="declaration-grid reveal">
        {% for doc in secessionDocs %}
        <article class="declaration-card">
          <header class="declaration-card__header">
            <span class="declaration-card__state">{{ doc.state }}</span>
            <span class="declaration-card__date">{{ doc.date }}</span>
          </header>
          <div class="declaration-card__counts">
            <div class="declaration-card__count declaration-card__count--slavery">
              <span class="declaration-card__number">{{ doc.slaveryMentions }}</span>
              <span class="declaration-card__label">slavery mentions</span>
            </div>
            <div class="declaration-card__count declaration-card__count--tariff">
              <span class="declaration-card__number">{{ doc.tariffMentions }}</span>
              <span class="declaration-card__label">tariff mentions</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <blockquote class="declaration-card__quote">"{{ doc.keyQuote }}"</blockquote>
          <footer class="declaration-card__footer">
            <a href="{{ doc.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="declaration-card__link">Read full text →</a>
            <a href="{{ doc.archiveUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="declaration-card__archive">Archived</a>
          </footer>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      <div class="declaration-summary reveal">
        <p class="declaration-summary__text">
          <strong>Total across all four declarations:</strong>
          <span class="declaration-summary__highlight">81 mentions of slavery</span>,
          <span class="declaration-summary__zero">0 mentions of tariffs</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# The Economic Reality #}
<section class="chapter chapter--muted" id="chapter-economics" data-chapter="The Economics">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Economic Question</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">{{ economicContext.headline }}</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">{{ economicContext.subheadline }}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide">
      <div class="stat-grid reveal">
        {% for fact in economicContext.keyFacts %}
        <article class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-card__number">{{ fact.stat }}</span>
          <span class="stat-card__label">{{ fact.label }}</span>
          <p class="stat-card__context">{{ fact.context }}</p>
          <a href="{{ fact.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="stat-card__source">{{ fact.source }} →</a>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <div class="economics-tariffs">
        <h3 class="headline-section" style="font-size: 1.5rem;">{{ economicContext.tariffsContext.headline }}</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">{{ economicContext.tariffsContext.explanation }}</p>
        <div class="tariff-comparison">
          {% for item in economicContext.tariffsContext.comparison %}
          <div class="tariff-item">
            <strong class="tariff-term">{{ item.term }}</strong>
            <span class="tariff-count">{{ item.mentions }}</span>
            <span class="tariff-note">{{ item.note }}</span>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <p class="text-accent" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-style: italic;">{{ economicContext.tariffsContext.conclusion }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# The Quotes They Can't Spin - All Four States #}
<section class="chapter chapter--accent-dark" id="chapter-quotes" data-chapter="Their Words">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">In Their Own Words</span>
      <h2 class="headline-section">Four States. One Message.</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">Direct quotes from the official secession declarations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide">
      <div class="state-quotes-grid">
        {% for doc in secessionDocs %}
        <article class="state-quote-card reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 }}">
          <header class="state-quote-card__header">
            <span class="state-quote-card__state">{{ doc.state }}</span>
            <span class="state-quote-card__abbr">{{ doc.abbr }}</span>
          </header>
          <blockquote class="state-quote-card__quote">
            <div class="state-quote-card__icon">"</div>
            <p class="state-quote-card__text">{{ doc.keyQuote }}</p>
          </blockquote>
          <div class="state-quote-card__more">
            <details>
              <summary>More from {{ doc.state }}</summary>
              <ul class="state-quote-card__additional">
                {% for quote in doc.additionalQuotes %}
                <li>"{{ quote }}"</li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ul>
            </details>
          </div>
          <footer class="state-quote-card__footer">
            <a href="{{ doc.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read full declaration →</a>
          </footer>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <div class="takeaway-box">
        <span class="takeaway-box__label">Key Takeaway</span>
        <p class="takeaway-box__text">Four different states, four different documents, one consistent message: they were seceding to preserve slavery. The "states' rights" reframing came later.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 4: THE MAPS
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-maps" data-chapter="The Shift">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter III</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">The Party Realignment</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        Compare the same eleven states across 164 years. The coalition shift is undeniable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide reveal">
      <div class="map-comparison">
        <article class="map-panel">
          <h3 class="map-panel__title">1860: Before Secession</h3>
          <p class="map-panel__subtitle">Southern Democrats dominated. Lincoln won zero of these states.</p>
          <div class="state-grid">
            {% for state in states %}
              {% set realignment = null %}
              {% for r in stateRealignment %}
                {% if r.abbr == state.abbr %}
                  {% set realignment = r %}
                {% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
              {% set tileClass = "state-tile--dem" %}
              {% if state.winner1860 == "Constitutional Union" %}
                {% set tileClass = "state-tile--other" %}
              {% endif %}
              <button
                class="state-tile state-tile--interactive {{ tileClass }}"
                data-abbr="{{ state.abbr }}"
                data-state="{{ state.state }}"
                data-flip-year="{{ realignment.flipYear if realignment else '' }}"
                data-key-figure="{{ realignment.keyFigure if realignment else '' }}"
                data-key-figure-role="{{ realignment.keyFigureRole if realignment else '' }}"
                data-headline="{{ realignment.headline if realignment else '' }}"
                data-summary="{{ realignment.summary | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-quote="{{ realignment.quote | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-quote-attribution="{{ realignment.quoteAttribution | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-source-url="{{ realignment.sourceUrl if realignment else '' }}"
                data-events="{{ realignment.keyEvents | dump | escape if realignment else '[]' }}"
                aria-label="Click to learn about {{ state.state }}'s political realignment"
              >
                <span class="state-tile__abbr">{{ state.abbr }}</span>
                <span class="state-tile__party">{{ state.winner1860 | truncate(12, true, '') }}</span>
              </button>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="map-panel">
          <h3 class="map-panel__title">2024: After Realignment</h3>
          <p class="map-panel__subtitle">Ten of eleven now vote Republican. Virginia stands alone.</p>
          <div class="state-grid">
            {% for state in states %}
              {% set realignment = null %}
              {% for r in stateRealignment %}
                {% if r.abbr == state.abbr %}
                  {% set realignment = r %}
                {% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
              {% set tileClass = "state-tile--rep" %}
              {% if state.winner2024 == "Democratic" %}
                {% set tileClass = "state-tile--dem" %}
              {% endif %}
              <button
                class="state-tile state-tile--interactive {{ tileClass }}"
                data-abbr="{{ state.abbr }}"
                data-state="{{ state.state }}"
                data-flip-year="{{ realignment.flipYear if realignment else '' }}"
                data-key-figure="{{ realignment.keyFigure if realignment else '' }}"
                data-key-figure-role="{{ realignment.keyFigureRole if realignment else '' }}"
                data-headline="{{ realignment.headline if realignment else '' }}"
                data-summary="{{ realignment.summary | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-quote="{{ realignment.quote | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-quote-attribution="{{ realignment.quoteAttribution | escape if realignment else '' }}"
                data-source-url="{{ realignment.sourceUrl if realignment else '' }}"
                data-events="{{ realignment.keyEvents | dump | escape if realignment else '[]' }}"
                aria-label="Click to learn about {{ state.state }}'s political realignment"
              >
                <span class="state-tile__abbr">{{ state.abbr }}</span>
                <span class="state-tile__party">{{ state.winner2024 }}</span>
              </button>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <p class="map-instructions">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M15 15l-2 5L9 9l11 4-5 2zm0 0l5 5M7.188 2.239l.777 2.897M5.136 7.965l-2.898-.777M13.95 4.05l-2.122 2.122m-5.657 5.656l-2.12 2.122"/>
        </svg>
        Click any state to see when and why it flipped
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 5: THE TIMELINE
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-timeline" data-chapter="The Arc">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter IV</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">From Reconstruction to Civil Rights</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        A century of struggle. Every federal reckoning left an imprint on party coalitions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content reveal">
      <div class="timeline">
        {% for item in reconstruction %}
        <article class="timeline__item reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 }}">
          <span class="timeline__year">{{ item.period }}</span>
          <div class="timeline__content">
            <p>{{ item.content | safe }}</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 6: THE DATA
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-data" data-chapter="The Data">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter V</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">Coalition Trajectories</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        Track the Republican share of former Confederate states from 1860 to 2024.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide reveal">
      <div class="coalition-chart">
        {% for point in coalition %}
        <div class="chart-row reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 }}">
          <span class="chart-year">{{ point.year }}</span>
          <div class="chart-bar">
            <div class="chart-fill" style="width: {{ point.share }}%;" data-value="{{ point.share }}%"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="chart-annotation">
            <strong>{{ point.label }}</strong>
            <span>{{ point.description }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 7: TODAY
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-today" data-chapter="Today">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter VI</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">Voting Access Today</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        The battle over who votes continues in the former Confederacy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide reveal">
      <div class="impact-grid">
        {% for card in impactCards %}
        <article class="impact-card reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 }}">
          <span class="impact-card__state">{{ card.state }}</span>
          <div class="impact-card__stat">{{ card.stat }}</div>
          <h3 class="impact-card__title">{{ card.title }}</h3>
          <p class="impact-card__text">{{ card.content }}</p>
          <p class="impact-card__source">{{ card.source }}</p>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 8: THE CONSENSUS
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-consensus" data-chapter="Consensus">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter VII</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">What Historians Agree On</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        Major professional organizations summarize the consensus.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--wide reveal">
      <div class="card-grid">
        {% for item in consensus %}
        <article class="card reveal reveal--delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 }}">
          <h3 class="card__title">{{ item.organization }}</h3>
          <p class="card__text">
            {{ item.content | safe }}
          </p>
          <div class="card__links">
            <a href="{{ item.link }}" class="document-card__link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              {{ item.linkText }}
            </a>
            {% if item.archiveLink %}
            <a href="{{ item.archiveLink }}" class="card__archive" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Archived backup copy">
              Archived
            </a>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
          {% if item.isGovernment %}
          <p class="card__warning">{{ item.warning }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 9: CHECK FOR YOURSELF
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-verify" data-chapter="Verify">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
    <div class="chapter__content chapter__content--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Chapter VIII</span>
      <h2 class="headline-chapter">Don't Take Our Word For It</h2>
      <p class="subheadline">
        If this contradicts what you learned, good. Check the sources yourself.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter chapter--muted">
  <div class="fact-stack">
    <article class="fact-item reveal">
      <span class="fact-item__number">01</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">We Linked Every Claim</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        Every quote on this site links to the original document. Yale's Avalon Project,
        the National Archives, teaching archives at major universities. Click through.
        Read the full text. See if we're cherry-picking or if this is really what they said.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="fact-item reveal reveal--delay-1">
      <span class="fact-item__number">02</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">Textbooks Change. Documents Don't.</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        What you learned in school depended on when and where you went to school.
        Textbooks get rewritten. The Mississippi Declaration of Secession says
        the same thing it said in 1861.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="fact-item reveal reveal--delay-2">
      <span class="fact-item__number">03</span>
      <h3 class="fact-item__title">Question Everything, Including This</h3>
      <p class="fact-item__text">
        If you think we got something wrong, check the source and tell us. The goal
        isn't to win an argument. It's to get the history right.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================
   CHAPTER 10: BIBLIOGRAPHY
   ============================================ #}
<section class="chapter chapter--dark" id="chapter-bibliography" data-chapter="Bibliography">
  <div class="chapter__inner">
